entries.sourceEnglish: Which does your society value more?
Those who stay with the herd
Those who step away from the herd

Lucius from The Golden Ass by Apuleius

In Aesop's Fables, one reads: "An ass put on the skin of a lion and went around frightening all the animals. The ass saw a fox and tried to frighten her too, but she had heard his voice first, so she said to the ass, 'You can be sure that I too would have been afraid, if I had not already heard the sound of your bray'." The moral is:
The disenfranchised are forced to imitate those in power without ever attaining more power
A fool is still a fool regardless of how they are dressed
